1
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:13,420
♪The maple mark on your skin♪

2
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:17,040
♪The only proof we exist♪

3
00:00:18,210 --> 00:00:21,450
♪I stole you back from destiny♪

4
00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:24,430
♪But can I redeem myself♪

5
00:00:24,430 --> 00:00:26,540
♪I don't care what fate foretells♪

6
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:30,330
♪Or how rough the road may be♪

7
00:00:30,340 --> 00:00:33,280
♪Stay, I'll fight for you♪

8
00:00:33,610 --> 00:00:37,660
♪That's all I'll ever do♪

9
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:39,890
♪If life is just a show♪

10
00:00:39,890 --> 00:00:42,650
♪I'll stay with you till the end♪

11
00:00:42,650 --> 00:00:44,980
♪I'm scared we'll wake up alone♪

12
00:00:44,980 --> 00:00:47,960
♪So don't let this dream end♪

13
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:52,420
♪In my bones, in my heart♪

14
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:54,100
♪I know I'll have to leave♪

15
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:55,670
♪You must not leave my side♪

16
00:00:55,670 --> 00:00:57,260
♪No place can hold us in♪

17
00:00:57,260 --> 00:01:01,910
♪Not when it's you and me♪

18
00:01:06,890 --> 00:01:10,400
♪Forever♪

19
00:01:11,490 --> 00:01:15,250
♪In my soul♪

20
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:23,300
=This Palace Maid Isn't Very Calm=
=Episode 7=

21
00:01:26,350 --> 00:01:27,710
Before lunch,

22
00:01:27,710 --> 00:01:29,790
finish all this work.

23
00:01:30,070 --> 00:01:32,070
If you don't finish, you don't eat.

24
00:01:32,070 --> 00:01:34,400
Ms. Song, why do others get so little?

25
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:35,280
Why so much for me?

26
00:01:36,870 --> 00:01:38,840
Even laundry maids

27
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,760
have ranks.

28
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:44,400
You're the lowest here.

29
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:47,310
That's His Majesty's order.

30
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,840
Got a problem?

31
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:51,000
Go ask him yourself.

32
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,350
That wretched emperor.

33
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:53,430
What did you say?

34
00:01:53,430 --> 00:01:54,840
I said His Majesty is wise

35
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:56,070
and benevolent.

36
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:04,480
I thought I was the Chosen One,

37
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:07,920
ready to dominate
with my cheat codes.

38
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:10,800
Turns out one decree, and I'm here.

39
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:14,080
Knowing the plot means nothing.

40
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:19,590
Well, look who it is.

41
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,280
Weren't you the Dowager's favorite?

42
00:02:22,470 --> 00:02:25,000
Look at you now.

43
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:29,750
Oh, it's Ms. Chun.

44
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,520
After that mess,

45
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:36,800
thought you'd be expelled.

46
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:40,840
But you just got kicked
into the labor camp.

47
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:43,150
It seems

48
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,000
you still got connections.

49
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,310
These clothes

50
00:02:46,650 --> 00:02:47,960
must be spotless

51
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,840
by evening.

52
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:52,000
If I see a single stain,

53
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,360
you're dead.

54
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,400
I…

55
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,750
I thought the 14th Prince
and I had something.

56
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:15,710
He helped me when I was down.

57
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,360
He protected me.

58
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,560
Give it back.

59
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,400
I...

60
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,840
One more step.

61
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,400
Stop.

62
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:29,190
Hold on.

63
00:03:29,470 --> 00:03:31,520
One, two, three, four, five.

64
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:34,080
Make it to the end.

65
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,910
No herbal bath

66
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:38,590
she's no ordinary maid.

67
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:41,560
Her skills are extraordinary.

68
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:42,870
Since eating

69
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:44,430
her sugar-free snacks,

70
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:46,630
Mother has improved.

71
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,910
She isn't startled
at night anymore.

72
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:51,840
You're bewitched too.

73
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,270
Take her.

74
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,120
- Wait.
- Move.

75
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:55,080
Your Highness.

76
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:56,590
Help me.

77
00:03:56,590 --> 00:03:57,710
You jerk.

78
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:02,080
I can't believe he set me up.

79
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,240
That jerk.

80
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:05,360
That jerk.

81
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:07,080
That jerk.

82
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,150
Ye Jin.

83
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:11,960
Zhi Hui?

84
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:15,520
A few days ago,

85
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,510
I heard the 14th Prince

86
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:18,430
took you to the Cining Palace.

87
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:20,070
I was so happy I couldn't sleep.

88
00:04:20,070 --> 00:04:22,600
I wanted to visit once you settled in.

89
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:23,800
How did you

90
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,480
end up in the labor camp?

91
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:28,040
Did you offend the Emperor?

92
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,480
Long story.

93
00:04:30,310 --> 00:04:32,270
Things change fast.

94
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,440
Anyway,

95
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:36,430
I brought food.

96
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,070
Eat while it's warm.

97
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,000
Zhi Hui.

98
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,000
Can you do me a favor?

99
00:04:49,390 --> 00:04:51,680
Don't say that.

100
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,950
I owe you

101
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:54,680
more than I can ever repay.

102
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:56,270
Just say it.

103
00:04:56,270 --> 00:04:57,870
I'll do anything.

104
00:04:57,870 --> 00:04:59,190
Even walk through fire.

105
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:04,390
This is today's snack.

106
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,160
Lately,

107
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:08,390
nothing tastes right.

108
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:09,230
Your Highness,

109
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,190
the kitchen follows

110
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:12,830
Ye Jin's recipes exactly.

111
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,920
The portions and the heat
are all perfect.

112
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:19,120
I finally had a few
capable people around me.

113
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:21,000
He demoted her

114
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,040
without a word.

115
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:26,180
What a filial son.

116
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:29,580
His Majesty is just worried
about your health.

117
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:31,620
Worried about my health?

118
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:34,460
He's just mad at his brother

119
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:36,300
and using me as an excuse.

120
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:38,140
They are biological brothers,

121
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:40,580
yet they fight

122
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:42,820
like roosters all day.

123
00:05:42,860 --> 00:05:45,420
And I can't even intervene.

124
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:46,620
If I do,

125
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:49,700
I'm biased.

126
00:05:51,260 --> 00:05:53,140
Unlike the 14th Prince,

127
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:55,380
he wasn't raised by me.

128
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:58,260
So he thinks I favor his brother more.

129
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:00,300
They both

130
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:03,260
came from my own flesh and blood.

131
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:05,860
They're both my sons.

132
00:06:05,860 --> 00:06:07,420
I love them equally.

133
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,380
If I didn't support him,

134
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:11,940
he wouldn't be emperor.

135
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:15,900
Don't be upset, Your Highness.

136
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,780
It's bad for your health.

137
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:19,420
Forget it.

138
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,140
He's been like that
since he was a child.

139
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:23,060
If I stayed angry at him,

140
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:24,620
I'd be dead by now.

141
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:27,460
Clear this away.

142
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:28,660
They taste bad

143
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,900
and look annoying.

144
00:06:35,460 --> 00:06:37,610
Your Highness, Candidate Zhi Hui
requests an audience.

145
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:39,060
Saying she has something important

146
00:06:39,060 --> 00:06:40,620
to offer you.

147
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:42,660
A candidate who hasn't
met the Emperor?

148
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,460
What does she want with me?

149
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:45,860
I've always

150
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,720
disliked social climbers.

151
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:50,740
She says Miss Ye Jin

152
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:52,100
asked her to deliver

153
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:54,820
a manual for your continued treatment.

154
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:56,380
Bring her in.

155
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:57,260
Yes.

156
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:03,420
Greetings, Your Highness.

157
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,020
Rise.

158
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:07,500
I am here

159
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,220
at Ye Jin's request.

160
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:11,980
Though demoted,

161
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:13,860
she still worries about you.

162
00:07:13,970 --> 00:07:15,020
She worked day and night

163
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:17,100
to compile her

164
00:07:17,260 --> 00:07:18,900
medical knowledge

165
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:19,980
into this manual.

166
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:32,900
This book explains the causes of diabetes

167
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:35,100
and how to treat it based on body type.

168
00:07:35,340 --> 00:07:39,420
It includes diet, acupuncture,
and lifestyle changes.

169
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:41,340
Even sugar control tips,

170
00:07:41,340 --> 00:07:42,460
medicinal meal plans,

171
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:43,620
body type analysis,

172
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:45,540
charts for seasonal living,

173
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:46,700
and walking exercises.

174
00:07:47,220 --> 00:07:50,260
She says it's a collection

175
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:52,740
of her family's recipes

176
00:07:52,740 --> 00:07:54,340
combined with her own experience.

177
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:56,100
This isn't just a prescription.

178
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,100
It's a medical text.

179
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,700
Generations of work

180
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:02,060
went into this,

181
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:04,020
and she just

182
00:08:04,020 --> 00:08:05,660
gave it all.

183
00:08:05,820 --> 00:08:07,220
Miss Ye Jin said

184
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,500
a healer's purpose

185
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,700
is to save the world.

186
00:08:09,940 --> 00:08:12,100
She hopes this book eases your pain

187
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:14,180
and serves the people

188
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:17,140
in the future.

189
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:18,940
Such a big heart.

190
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:22,780
Not only a brilliant physician,

191
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,420
but also a girl of virtue.

192
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,900
She's worth more

193
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:27,780
than those
arrogant physicians combined.

194
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,300
Someone like her

195
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,820
must not be wasted.

196
00:08:32,820 --> 00:08:35,300
Ruizhu, take my decree

197
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:37,180
to the labor camp.

198
00:08:45,180 --> 00:08:48,140
This blood-stained robe
must be clean before dinner.

199
00:08:48,350 --> 00:08:49,620
If any trace,

200
00:08:49,780 --> 00:08:50,660
you'll pay for it.

201
00:08:51,460 --> 00:08:52,300
Get back.

202
00:08:53,060 --> 00:08:54,100
You throwing that at me?

203
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:55,460
You wretch.

204
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:56,780
Why are you shouting?

205
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:58,660
Ms. Song,

206
00:08:58,660 --> 00:09:00,100
she's being disobedient.

207
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:01,780
Teach her a lesson.

208
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:05,420
No dinner for you.

209
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:06,740
Fine.

210
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:09,420
I haven't eaten dinner
since I got here anyway.

211
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:13,060
Then no meals tomorrow either.

212
00:09:13,130 --> 00:09:13,980
Fine.

213
00:09:13,980 --> 00:09:15,140
If I'm starving,

214
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:16,460
I quit.

215
00:09:17,220 --> 00:09:18,180
Get back here.

216
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,540
Sharp tongue.

217
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:23,100
Dare talk back?

218
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,260
Do you know

219
00:09:24,260 --> 00:09:26,660
your life's in her hands here?

220
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:28,020
Shut up.

221
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:29,100
Who are you hitting?

222
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:30,180
You…

223
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:31,100
How bold.

224
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:32,420
You're the bold one.

225
00:09:32,860 --> 00:09:34,220
As the head maid,

226
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:35,220
you're abusing power

227
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:36,340
and taking bribes.

228
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:38,060
Those earrings,

229
00:09:38,060 --> 00:09:39,220
necklace,

230
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:40,580
gold bracelet,

231
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,900
jade pin,

232
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:42,980
and the banknotes

233
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:43,980
hidden in your trunk

234
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:45,540
are all proof of your corruption.

235
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:49,820
I'm officially reporting you.

236
00:09:50,180 --> 00:09:51,220
In broad daylight,

237
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:53,300
everyone here can testify.

238
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,140
You…

239
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:55,100
Guards.

240
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:56,380
Shut her up.

241
00:09:56,380 --> 00:09:58,140
You've got a lot of nerve.

242
00:10:01,740 --> 00:10:03,500
Miss Ruizhu, it's Ye Jin.

243
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:04,860
She's being unruly.

244
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,060
I was disciplining her.

245
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,300
By order of the Empress Dowager.

246
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:11,580
Maid Ye Jin

247
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:13,100
has shown loyalty

248
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,340
and extraordinary medical skill.

249
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:16,380
She is a rare talent.

250
00:10:16,460 --> 00:10:17,980
Her contribution of the manual

251
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:18,900
is a great service.

252
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,340
As of today,

253
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:21,700
she leaves the labor camp

254
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:23,140
to serve as a court physician.

255
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,900
Allowed to practice
in the inner palace.

256
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:26,700
I thank the Empress Dowager
for her grace.

257
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:30,740
The Dowager hates corruption.

258
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:33,560
Song, come with me
to the Department of Justice

259
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:34,700
and explain yourself.

260
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,020
Eunuch Fu.

261
00:10:49,460 --> 00:10:50,900
Well, if it isn't Physician Shen.

262
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,260
Congratulations.

263
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:53,740
In just a few days,

264
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:55,500
you went from a labor camp maid

265
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:58,020
to a sixth-rank physician.

266
00:10:58,660 --> 00:11:00,860
I am truly

267
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:02,700
impressed.

268
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,220
You're joking.

269
00:11:04,220 --> 00:11:05,740
It was just luck

270
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:07,460
and the Empress Dowager's grace.

271
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:08,820
You're back.

272
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:10,700
Your Highness.

273
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:12,500
Greetings, Prince.

274
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,700
Disappointed

275
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,340
to see me alive?

276
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:20,700
Why say that?

277
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:22,700
If not for you,

278
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,940
I wouldn't have gone there.

279
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:28,060
So,

280
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:29,900
you figured it out.

281
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:32,380
Sooner than I expected.

282
00:11:32,740 --> 00:11:33,900
You are capable.

283
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,100
I trusted you.

284
00:11:37,420 --> 00:11:39,300
Why set me up?

285
00:11:40,740 --> 00:11:41,900
You think

286
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:43,900
I harmed you?

287
00:11:44,260 --> 00:11:45,380
Didn't you?

288
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,740
This palace

289
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:52,660
is a gilded cage.

290
00:11:53,140 --> 00:11:56,020
Even Mother

291
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:57,900
is bound by rules.

292
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:59,700
You're a newcomer

293
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:00,660
who showed

294
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:01,580
too much talent.

295
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:03,580
If you had risen too fast,

296
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,780
the labor camp would've

297
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,370
been the least of your problems.

298
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:10,220
Because of our bond,

299
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:12,980
I pushed you into a trap

300
00:12:13,140 --> 00:12:15,020
to see if you could climb out.

301
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,100
And to see

302
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:22,300
what you rely on.

303
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:24,940
And did you see?

304
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:27,180
Miss Ye Jin,

305
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:28,820
your thoughts run too deep.

306
00:12:29,460 --> 00:12:30,900
You're hard to read.

307
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:32,860
But I see you clearly.

308
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:35,780
You're moody,

309
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:36,740
calculating,

310
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:38,060
and you treat people

311
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,580
like chess pieces.

312
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:41,700
It's my fault.

313
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:45,060
I was blinded by your charm

314
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,660
and mistook you for someone I knew.

315
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:48,140
I wasted my feelings on you.

316
00:12:48,620 --> 00:12:49,820
But now

317
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:50,940
I understand.

318
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:52,340
Someone like you

319
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:53,420
is to be admired from afar,

320
00:12:53,420 --> 00:12:54,580
not trusted.

321
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:56,060
From now on,

322
00:12:56,140 --> 00:12:57,580
we go our separate ways.

323
00:12:57,580 --> 00:12:58,980
No more crossing paths.

324
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,880
♪I am but an outsider♪

325
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:17,080
♪Yet something drags me deeper♪

326
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:21,360
♪Outwit the world but not the way we meet♪

327
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:25,600
♪Splendid blooms line deadly ground♪

328
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:33,120
♪Life's a phantom, yet I find you♪

329
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:36,680
♪In a world of lies, you're all that's clear♪

330
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:39,200
♪I know how this story ends♪

331
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:43,760
♪I still want what's in your eyes♪

332
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:48,200
♪Truth or lie—I can't tell♪

333
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:56,480
♪You hide it all behind your lines♪

334
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:59,760
♪So familiar, yet out of reach♪

335
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:03,040
♪A history that no one can search♪

336
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:06,560
♪Like you drift in from another star♪

337
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,360
♪I am but an outsider♪

338
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:10,600
♪Yet something drags me deeper♪

339
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:14,640
♪Outwit the world but not the way we meet♪

340
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:19,320
♪Splendid blooms line deadly ground♪

341
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:26,640
♪Life's a phantom, yet I find you♪

342
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:30,000
♪In a world of lies, you're all that's clear♪

343
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,480
♪I know how this story ends♪

344
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:36,640
♪I still want what's in your eyes♪

345
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:39,920
♪When it's over and I'm gone♪

346
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:43,720
♪Please forget me and move on♪

347
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:49,960
♪Just let this absurd dream fade♪

348
00:14:53,120 --> 00:15:01,480
♪Snow hides our tracks♪

349
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:14,760
♪When do I finally wake♪
